      <div class="question">What is Silent?</div>
      <div class="answer">
        Silent allows you to create online spaces where people gather together to show camaraderie.
        <br><br>
        Digital communication today is being simplified, and modularized. You can see this trajectory from Facebook, to Twitter, to Snapchat, to Yo: each new service focuses more specifically and more minimally on a certain type of communication.
        <br><br>
        Silent gets to the core of online togetherness, foregoing content entirely, and making everything about the comfort of each other’s presence.
        <br><br>
        <strong>Silent is currently in Beta.</strong>
      </div>
      <br><br>

      <div class="question">How does it work?</div>
      <div class="answer">
        Silent is really easy. 
        <br><br>
        First, choose a unique room name. When you do this, you’ll create a unique URL which becomes your new online room. This URL is your room’s identity, so if you made the room Cat_Lovers, your URL would be silent.buzz/@Cat_Lovers.
        <br><br>
        Share this URL with your friends, and you’ll see them join your room as they go online. Remember, Silent keeps its users silent; it’s not about what you say, but the community your online presence creates.
        <br><br>
        Every room keeps track of the number of people in it at a time, and the total number of people who have ever been in that room. You can also find the most popular rooms through Silent’s trending list!
      </div>
      <br><br>

